body_html:
Yes, will try 3.5 whl out again today.

Re bonus: Nice! :)

Sent from my iPhone

On Sep 14, 2016, at 6:20 PM, gunan notifications@github.com wrote:

Bonus, we found out that our proto packages were not optimized when building. Now we are.
I have built and uploaded all the following packages, this time with correct python versions:
https://storage.googleapis.com/tensorflow/mac/cpu/protobuf-3.0.0-cp35-cp35m-macosx_10_11_x86_64.whl
https://storage.googleapis.com/tensorflow/mac/cpu/protobuf-3.0.0-cp27-cp27m-macosx_10_11_x86_64.whl

https://storage.googleapis.com/tensorflow/linux/cpu/protobuf-3.0.0-cp27-none-linux_x86_64.whl
https://storage.googleapis.com/tensorflow/linux/cpu/protobuf-3.0.0-cp34-cp34m-linux_x86_64.whl
https://storage.googleapis.com/tensorflow/linux/cpu/protobuf-3.0.0-cp35-cp35m-linux_x86_64.whl

But there is a problem building the py3.4 version on mac. I am exploring what is going on.

In the meantime, could you try using the py3.5 version by renaming, and see if it works?

—
